reviews.review:
A disappointment, but not a surprise.
There are parts of the movie that I didn't hate. Rey finally struggled with something and generally acted closer to what we expect from a human being. Kylo was more of a respectable villain and less of a kid throwing a tantrum. Poe and Finn actually did something useful and advanced the plot. The good guys actually had a chance to interact with each other, but not a lot, as the movie really rushed to get all of its convoluted plot points checked off the list and all the mcguffins placed in right hands. Everything to do with Palpatine's comeback is dumb - his return, his plan, his (hopefully final) demise. I hated the whole ending. He shouldn't even be in this movie.
I loved the ending , actually is perfect , but there was so many things that can be explained better

Damn near pitch perfect ending to the saga. While I would have done a few things differently I has 0 problems with the direction they went. I thought I would hate it after TLJ they redirected in a perfect way.
THERE ARE NO WORDS FOR HOW TERRIBLE THIS WAS!!!!!
Such an amazing ending.....not just to a movie, but to an entire life of work! Maybe a good beginning too, “let’s see.”

A very fast paced, and exciting Star Wars movie. If you're a huge fan like me, you will love all the details and Easter eggs relating to previous movies. I was only upset about some minor decisions made in the movie. Would have made a couple small changes to the ending, if it were my decision. All in all a beautiful movie, and a great ending for the story of Skywalker.
Good conclusion to a fantastic saga

Absolutely fantastic way to end the saga, my favorite of the new trilogy and my 4th favorite of the entire saga. A very cathartic ending. I went through the entirety of the emotional spectrum I laughed, I cheered I shed a tear. Good job JJ Abrams.

It was fine for a tweens holiday adventure movie and the acting was reasonable but it is not a Star Wars film. OK for non-fans as a piece of adventure fluff but if you are over 14 it's not worth seeing.
